1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

2
00:00:06,200 --> 00:00:08,520
{\an8}<i>Dear God, the Most Gracious,
the Most Merciful,</i>

3
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:12,920
{\an8}I beg and plead to You

4
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:18,639
{\an8}let not even the thought of divorce
cross my heart

5
00:00:18,640 --> 00:00:20,600
{\an8}or mind from this day forward.

6
00:00:21,680 --> 00:00:26,280
{\an8}May my marriage to Thariq endure
until the end of my days.

7
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:33,600
{\an8}And if the time has come,
let me be the one to go first.

8
00:00:34,760 --> 00:00:39,880
{\an8}I am too weak to continue life on
this earth without him by my side.

9
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:45,000
Dear God,

10
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:49,359
grant me the chance and the strength

11
00:00:49,360 --> 00:00:53,560
to win back the heart of Thariq Ridzuwan.

12
00:00:55,120 --> 00:00:57,480
Amen.

13
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:05,519
All right, ma'am. I've received
the result from your blood test.

14
00:01:06,160 --> 00:01:08,040
Everything looks normal.

15
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:09,919
Thank God.

16
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:11,039
Ma'am,

17
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:14,759
you didn't tell us that you're expecting.

18
00:01:14,760 --> 00:01:17,360
- Expecting?
- You didn't know?

19
00:01:17,960 --> 00:01:19,559
What?

20
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:21,760
You're seven weeks pregnant.

21
00:01:22,520 --> 00:01:24,959
All praise to God. Congratulations, ma'am.

22
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:28,000
- I'll excuse myself.
- Doctor.

23
00:01:29,360 --> 00:01:31,640
Can I ask you a favor?

24
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:34,840
Please don't tell my husband.

25
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:37,079
May I know why?

26
00:01:37,080 --> 00:01:38,880
It's just...

27
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:42,120
I'm actually really angry
at him right now.

28
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:47,760
- All right, then. I should get going.
- Sure.

29
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:51,360
All praise to God.

30
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:54,200
Thank you, God.

31
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:02,640
Baby,

32
00:02:03,240 --> 00:02:06,200
help me win Dad back.

33
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,600
{\an8}We can't see the face.

34
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:26,479
{\an8}- Are there other angles?
- There aren't.

35
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:28,719
{\an8}He knows all the camera locations.

36
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:31,120
{\an8}Which means, he knows the CCTV angles too.

37
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:34,280
This man isn't ordinary.

38
00:02:35,480 --> 00:02:38,479
Daniel, what about the hotel's CCTVs?

39
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:41,839
Unfortunately, every single footage
from that week has been corrupted.

40
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:43,160
So, yeah. Nothing.

41
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:47,959
Damn it. It must be Farez.

42
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:50,760
I did some digging on
Radwa's sister's social media.

43
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:53,439
And it seems like
there are quite a lot of DMs

44
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:55,559
from this particular guy.

45
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:58,520
Lots of flirting and sexual talk.

46
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:03,559
What else do we have, Kevin?

47
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:06,079
Actually, all the footages
from all those hotels.

48
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:08,160
And look at what I found.

49
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:26,679
So, we have proof.

50
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:29,239
Raudhah checked into this hotel
with the same guy.

51
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:32,440
And she bumped into Thariq at this hotel.

52
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:36,240
This is still not enough
to clear his name.

53
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:41,520
Megat, can you replay
that video of the accident?

54
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:47,760
Stop.

55
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:51,680
He looked at the driver.

56
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:55,040
He was facing the car's dashcam.

57
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:59,240
I think we can see his face
from the dashcam.

58
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:04,599
If we can match the guy in the dashcam

59
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:06,480
with the guy at the hotel...

60
00:04:08,640 --> 00:04:10,000
Checkmate.

61
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:15,760
Megat, Daniel, find the car.

62
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:19,760
Kevin, keep digging on the hotel guy.

63
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:23,480
Where's Haider?

64
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:36,200
That's a great tactic
to make someone pass out.

65
00:04:57,360 --> 00:05:00,120
- What do you want?
- I want you to apologize.

66
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:03,879
- No.
- You ran away from the hospital.

67
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:07,360
You didn't even let me know.
Do you like making me worried?

68
00:05:08,080 --> 00:05:10,400
I went to work. Not playing futsal.

69
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:14,239
- You could have told me.
- The mission is P&C.

70
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:16,840
I don't care. Apologize right now.

71
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:20,679
- No. I didn't do anything wrong.
- Apologize now!

72
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:21,840
Why should I?

73
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:24,959
Apologize, or else...

74
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:27,159
Or else what?

75
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:30,519
I've been through torture
with all kinds of bad men.

76
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:32,919
There's nothing you can do
to break me, Thalia.

77
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:35,599
- Nothing.
- I'm pretty sure no one

78
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,679
- had ever done this to you.
- Sure?

79
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:38,959
I am.

80
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:41,160
Try me.

81
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:49,599
Dear.

82
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:51,279
- Don't do this.
- No!

83
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:54,959
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

84
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:58,880
- I was just kidding.
- I'm your wife, Haider.

85
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:05,399
Of course I'd be worried if the guy
I love the most went missing.

86
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,879
I didn't go missing.

87
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:11,280
I'm here right now.
Don't cry. I can't do this.

88
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:13,999
I can't handle tears.

89
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:17,000
If even the Great Wall of China
can collapse, I'm even worse.

90
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:21,079
I looked for you like a crazy person.

91
00:06:21,080 --> 00:06:22,920
I thought you were dead!

92
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:25,679
If you die, I want to die too!

93
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:27,639
- Don't.
- Don't?

94
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,599
I can't. Don't you love me?

95
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:32,240
- Why?
- Not me, it's Thariq.

96
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:33,999
- Thariq?
- Ridz.

97
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:37,239
He said not to answer the phone
if you called.

98
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:38,480
It's Ridz.

99
00:06:41,320 --> 00:06:43,320
Peace be upon you.

100
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:45,719
And peace be upon you.

101
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:47,880
It's been a while.

102
00:06:49,640 --> 00:06:51,159
I know.

103
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:55,960
Lately, I've been a little grumpy,
I forgot to include you in my prayers.

104
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:59,240
- I'm sorry.
- Yeah.

105
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:04,000
I made fried rice.
I was about to serve it and you came home.

106
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:08,640
It's been a while since I last fed you.

107
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:20,640
I have good news about your sister.

108
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:23,200
You don't have to.

109
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,640
You don't have to prove anything to me.

110
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:33,960
I trust you. Since then, now, and forever.

111
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:39,799
What else did I do wrong?

112
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:41,560
Why are you looking at me like that?

113
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:47,040
Watching you heals me.

114
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:53,440
Are you mixed or something?

115
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:59,439
- You resemble someone.
- What do you mean?

116
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:02,119
- I'm sure you are.
- I don't.

117
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:04,720
Half me, half you.

118
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:10,240
You look a bit like our future child.

119
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:12,720
What?

120
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:24,480
I miss you, Thariq Ridzuwan.

121
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:30,120
I miss you even more, darling.

122
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:35,880
I want to go home, please.

123
00:08:37,039 --> 00:08:37,959
Please.

124
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:40,959
Darling, this house is safe enough.

125
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:43,200
I will be safe wherever you are.

126
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:46,199
Please, dear.

127
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:49,479
I promise I will stick with you
all the time.

128
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:53,400
I will do everything by your side.

129
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:58,880
- Please, dear.
- You're so annoying and short.

130
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:01,920
What did you say?

131
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:08,360
- What did you say?
- No, I was saying

132
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:13,240
- you're short on...
- On?

133
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:15,600
Nothing.

134
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:17,359
Nothing?

135
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:19,720
Right.

136
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:22,680
I have all the money.

137
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:25,760
This must be how you see me.

138
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:29,679
My feet hurt.

139
00:09:29,680 --> 00:09:31,440
So, can I go home?

140
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:39,600
My body feels sore. I feel dizzy.

141
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:43,759
It's okay, dear. I'll give you a massage.

142
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:44,880
Yes.

143
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:49,959
Dear, I missed you.

144
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:51,720
Yes.

145
00:09:52,680 --> 00:09:53,959
Dear.

146
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:56,160
I said I missed you!

147
00:09:57,200 --> 00:10:00,840
Yes, I missed you too, treasure.

148
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:03,400
Okay.

149
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:14,560
- What now?
- Dear, I'm hungry.

150
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:17,480
You just ate.

151
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:19,919
That was then.

152
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:21,120
I'm hungry again.

153
00:10:22,760 --> 00:10:25,360
You eat like you're eating for two.

154
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,640
No wonder you're chubby.

155
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:30,000
What?

156
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:31,560
What?

157
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:33,960
What did you say?

158
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:44,159
Nothing. I said nothing.

159
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:50,040
I was just scrolling on my social media,
and it was nothing.

160
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:53,800
I'll go and get you some food. Wait here.

161
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:57,200
It was nothing.

162
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,920
Do I look chubby?

163
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,880
So close.

164
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:10,440
Chicken rice.

165
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:38,559
- What now?
- I don't want you to leave.

166
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:41,039
I'm not going anywhere. I'll be here.

167
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:42,640
Go on and eat.

168
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:48,800
Feed me.

169
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,559
If you won't, never mind.

170
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:58,680
- I can feed myself.
- I'll do it.

171
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:01,440
Don't make that face.

172
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:08,200
- In the name of God...
- The Most Gracious, the Most Merciful.

173
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,400
Sorry.

174
00:12:36,040 --> 00:12:37,480
Dear?

175
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:39,960
I...

176
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:43,320
- What is this smell?
- Dear?

177
00:12:43,920 --> 00:12:44,920
Dear!

178
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,360
Dear...

179
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:00,120
Are you okay?

180
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:07,360
I'm okay.

181
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:11,079
I don't know why I'm like this today.

182
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:14,279
I can't see or smell chicken rice.

183
00:13:14,280 --> 00:13:15,480
I feel nauseous.

184
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:22,119
Why didn't you tell me?

185
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:24,040
I can eat it by myself.

186
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:26,120
It's okay.

187
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:29,959
Even if I were on my deathbed,
I would still feed you.

188
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:32,000
As long as you're happy.

189
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:40,159
I wonder what I did for God
to send you to me as a gift.

190
00:13:40,160 --> 00:13:41,559
Me too.

191
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:44,119
I wonder what I did
to be given a strong wife like you

192
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:46,560
as a gift from God.

193
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:52,680
Thank you for staying until now.

194
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:59,400
I hope all your pain will be replaced
with happiness.

195
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:02,080
- Amen.
- Amen.

196
00:14:06,560 --> 00:14:08,160
I'm sorry.

197
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:28,079
- What else do you want from me?
- Don't you dare ask me that.

198
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:29,999
This is all your fault!

199
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:33,279
You know you can't conceive,
but you still want to get married.

200
00:14:33,280 --> 00:14:36,839
Your husband took advantage of your sister
because he wants a child so badly.

201
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:39,200
- It wasn't Ridz's child!
- Hey!

202
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:42,079
Raudhah told me everything!

203
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:43,879
Now, I want him to be responsible.

204
00:14:43,880 --> 00:14:45,719
It's not his responsibility.

205
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:48,480
If he has a child, it should be with me,
not another woman!

206
00:14:49,760 --> 00:14:54,840
You're not only barren,
but you're also rude!

207
00:14:56,280 --> 00:14:59,440
Mom! Don't touch my wife.

208
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:03,359
I can do whatever I want.
She's my daughter.

209
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:06,279
I can do whatever I want to her.

210
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:09,080
- Who are you?
- I'm his husband. Why?

211
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:12,879
Since when did you consider me
your daughter?

212
00:15:12,880 --> 00:15:15,599
- Darling, go upstairs.
- I won't.

213
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:17,959
It's not your fault.
Why do you have to be responsible?

214
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:20,399
Darling, go upstairs.
I'll settle this with Mom.

215
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,560
No! I don't want you to marry Raudhah!

216
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:26,239
Stop your drama!

217
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:30,959
Listen, even if you bleed tears,
do you think I'll pity you?

218
00:15:30,960 --> 00:15:32,759
Mom, go home.

219
00:15:32,760 --> 00:15:34,839
I'll come over to your house
to discuss tonight.

220
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:36,159
Leave. Go.

221
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:37,479
I'll go.

222
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:40,680
But if you don't come, you're done!

223
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:48,519
- Dear.
- It's okay.

224
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:50,760
Listen to me. It's fine.

225
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:52,919
Forgive them.

226
00:15:52,920 --> 00:15:54,839
- Just forgive them.
- Forgive them?

227
00:15:54,840 --> 00:15:56,679
- It's not a big deal.
- It is a big deal.

228
00:15:56,680 --> 00:15:59,840
Forgive them. Please.

229
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:07,240
That's okay.

230
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:09,680
I'm coming with you.

231
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:12,640
Darling, stay here.

232
00:16:14,480 --> 00:16:16,840
No. I don't want you to marry Raudhah.

233
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:19,959
Me marrying Raudhah?
No way. It's disgusting.

234
00:16:19,960 --> 00:16:24,559
You don't understand.
They would do anything for Raudhah.

235
00:16:24,560 --> 00:16:27,199
And you don't understand
that I'd do anything for you.

236
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:28,640
All right? Okay?

237
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:32,520
Thariq Ridzuwan!

238
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:35,359
You kidnapped my husband
from the hospital!

239
00:16:35,360 --> 00:16:38,479
You stopped him
from answering my calls too, right?

240
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:39,640
Who said that?

241
00:16:40,480 --> 00:16:41,960
It was Haider.

242
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:46,239
It was true. I told him to.

243
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:48,199
I apologized. So, it's fair.

244
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:49,600
What?

245
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:53,240
What do you mean by fair?
There's no such thing.

246
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:58,640
But I'll let you go.
Because Radwa is cute!

247
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:01,400
- Peace be upon you.
- And peace be upon you.

248
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:05,318
Why did they get to come?

249
00:17:05,319 --> 00:17:08,400
Because if they're not there,
I can't prove my innocence.

250
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:12,720
Radwa, Kevin and I
will keep you company at home.

251
00:17:14,480 --> 00:17:15,440
Where's that guy?

252
00:17:16,040 --> 00:17:17,800
In the car, sleeping.

253
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:19,880
Darling,

254
00:17:20,599 --> 00:17:24,200
I promise, after tonight,
your family won't disturb you.

255
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:25,800
Okay?

256
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:30,360
Boys, let's go.

257
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:44,720
Okay, girls! It's girls' night!

258
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:15,480
Ridz!

259
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:17,200
What are you doing here?

260
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:20,800
- Ridz.
- Raudhah.

261
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:27,840
- You're here.
- What are you doing?

262
00:18:29,080 --> 00:18:31,000
I didn't expect that to be Raudhah.

263
00:18:32,240 --> 00:18:35,920
Because the Raudhah I know
doesn't wear sexy clothes.

264
00:18:37,160 --> 00:18:38,720
And she's not drunk.

265
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:43,920
Your name doesn't suit your behavior.

266
00:18:44,520 --> 00:18:47,240
I wanted to take her home.
But she refused.

267
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:49,520
She didn't want you
to find out that she's drunk.

268
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:53,160
That's why I took the initiative

269
00:18:54,080 --> 00:18:55,480
to book a room for her.

270
00:18:57,280 --> 00:18:58,240
What?

271
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:01,799
And that was when
you took advantage of her, wasn't it?

272
00:19:01,800 --> 00:19:03,920
She was drunk!

273
00:19:04,840 --> 00:19:07,999
That's rape! You're an animal!
Where's your brain?

274
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,880
Rape?

275
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:12,359
It wasn't.

276
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:13,520
I left her at the lobby.

277
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:16,400
The hotel settled everything.

278
00:19:17,360 --> 00:19:20,480
Do you have proof
that it wasn't your child?

279
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:25,760
Ma'am, what's the proof
that it was Ridz's child?

280
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:30,000
Mom, ask your daughter.

281
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:33,519
Raudhah,

282
00:19:33,520 --> 00:19:38,160
is it Ridz's child, or someone else's?

283
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:43,519
Yes, he raped me that night!

284
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:45,239
Did you hear that?

285
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:48,120
What else are you denying?

286
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:53,599
You're lucky Mom only asked you
to divorce Radwa and marry Raudhah.

287
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:56,159
If it was me,
I would've made a police report

288
00:19:56,160 --> 00:19:59,119
so you'd end up in jail, you animal!

289
00:19:59,120 --> 00:20:01,799
- What do you want?
- I was wondering if this is

290
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:04,079
what evil looks like, disguised as human.

291
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:06,119
So ugly. What an eyesore.

292
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:07,200
Enough.

293
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:11,800
Why do you hate me so much?

294
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:16,599
I don't care if you do this to me,

295
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:19,239
but you're dragging Radwa into it,
and I don't like it.

296
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:21,279
It's always Radwa!

297
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:23,879
You're giving me a headache!

298
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:27,479
What does she have
that you can't leave her?

299
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:29,080
Because she...

300
00:20:30,640 --> 00:20:32,560
is my wife.

301
00:20:33,480 --> 00:20:35,520
No one can replace her. Do you understand?

302
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:37,479
Listen.

303
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:41,399
I don't know how she manipulated you

304
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:43,319
into becoming like her too.

305
00:20:43,320 --> 00:20:48,079
My mom said not to say filthy words

306
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:49,720
unless you want blisters.

307
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:51,919
What's your problem?

308
00:20:51,920 --> 00:20:55,119
Mom and I have made our decision.

309
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:59,960
You have to divorce Radwa
and marry Raudhah.

310
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:02,800
What are you saying, Dad?

311
00:21:04,840 --> 00:21:08,039
Don't make me lose my respect for you.

312
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:11,719
You can't even prove
that it's not your child.

313
00:21:11,720 --> 00:21:13,680
So you have to marry her!

314
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:18,680
I won't let it happen.

315
00:21:20,160 --> 00:21:24,959
Mr. Husaini, what made you think
I would let my husband

316
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:26,440
marry that woman?

317
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:31,399
Why are you so rude?
Do you want to be a rebellious daughter?

318
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:34,359
My husband is my heaven. I obey him.

319
00:21:34,360 --> 00:21:35,839
He said he doesn't want to marry Raudhah.

320
00:21:35,840 --> 00:21:36,880
Don't you understand?

321
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:43,719
Dear, I'll clean this mess tonight.

322
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:47,280
After tonight, I don't want to have
anything to do with this family.

323
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:52,439
You saved me. You healed me.

324
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:54,159
Now, they're taking you away from me?

325
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:57,160
No. I'll never let that happen.

326
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,559
I don't want to lose you again.

327
00:22:00,560 --> 00:22:04,559
I've hurt enough. Enough.

328
00:22:04,560 --> 00:22:07,319
Listen to me, darling.

329
00:22:07,320 --> 00:22:10,919
No one can take me away from you.

330
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:15,239
Darling, never be controlled
by your money,

331
00:22:15,240 --> 00:22:18,359
your past, and people.

332
00:22:18,360 --> 00:22:20,760
Put your trust in God.

333
00:22:24,360 --> 00:22:26,920
Whatever your decision is tonight,

334
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:32,280
I will follow.
I believe in you, my treasure.

335
00:22:34,280 --> 00:22:35,480
Okay?

336
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:38,360
Go.

337
00:22:44,640 --> 00:22:46,600
When I was young,

338
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:49,120
I've always been scared of ghosts.

339
00:22:51,120 --> 00:22:52,800
But now that I'm older,

340
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:56,079
I realize that humans

341
00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:58,520
are far scarier.

342
00:22:59,760 --> 00:23:01,680
But the saddest part is that

343
00:23:02,520 --> 00:23:05,200
the humans are my own family.

344
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:09,359
- Rude!
- Radwa, help me.

345
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:13,039
I'm your sister. Don't you pity me?

346
00:23:13,040 --> 00:23:15,440
You're heartless.

347
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:20,359
You didn't think
of saving your family's name?

348
00:23:20,360 --> 00:23:22,800
Then why didn't you protect
the family's name in the first place?

349
00:23:23,920 --> 00:23:25,760
Ask your husband
to divorce you and marry her.

350
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:28,400
Enough!

351
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:31,159
Listen to me!

352
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:34,079
Thariq Ridzuwan is my husband alone!

353
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:35,680
That's final!

354
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:39,919
Find another man to be responsible.

355
00:23:39,920 --> 00:23:42,399
You keep saying that!

356
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:43,799
Right now,

357
00:23:43,800 --> 00:23:47,919
he can't even prove it wasn't his child!

358
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:50,160
- Do you understand?
- Boys.

359
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:53,240
Get the monkey out.

360
00:23:53,920 --> 00:23:55,600
Just wait.

361
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:31,160
Baby?

362
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:34,439
Oh, God. You're hurt.

363
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:39,000
Baby, what happened to you?
Tell me who did this to you?

364
00:24:40,360 --> 00:24:44,159
Your baby is the father of that child.

365
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:45,640
Don't be rude!

366
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:48,759
Because he couldn't get you pregnant,

367
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:50,760
he got your sister pregnant.

368
00:24:51,560 --> 00:24:53,919
You call someone barren,
you don't even have a child yourself.

369
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:55,119
- You!
- Enough!

370
00:24:55,120 --> 00:24:56,519
Touch her and I'll break your arms.

371
00:24:56,520 --> 00:24:58,360
Ask her to watch her mouth!

372
00:24:59,120 --> 00:25:01,359
All of you!

373
00:25:01,360 --> 00:25:06,919
Do you have proof that the child was his?

374
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:08,279
Auntie.

375
00:25:08,280 --> 00:25:11,799
Just look at your daughter. She's pale.

376
00:25:11,800 --> 00:25:15,320
Only guilty people look like that.

377
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:19,519
Baby,

378
00:25:19,520 --> 00:25:21,320
you didn't do it, right?

379
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:27,319
You didn't do it, right?
It wasn't your baby, right?

380
00:25:27,320 --> 00:25:29,639
No, dear.

381
00:25:29,640 --> 00:25:32,159
They're accusing me.

382
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:35,000
- See, it was an accusation!
- Accusation?

383
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:41,440
- What's this?
- The proof.

384
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:08,119
It wasn't just a one-time thing.

385
00:26:08,120 --> 00:26:11,040
They sleep together every month.

386
00:26:16,160 --> 00:26:19,280
Baby.

387
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:22,719
Baby?

388
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:25,519
What have you done?

389
00:26:25,520 --> 00:26:27,559
- What have you done?
- Stop it.

390
00:26:27,560 --> 00:26:30,879
- Enough!
- What do you mean, enough?

391
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:32,679
Stop it! Don't hit her!

392
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:35,000
Are you crazy, Mom?

393
00:26:36,200 --> 00:26:40,880
Are you crazy? Or am I crazy?
I don't know.

394
00:26:43,320 --> 00:26:44,520
Stop!

395
00:26:46,320 --> 00:26:48,000
Do you have anything to say?

396
00:26:49,120 --> 00:26:51,320
Do you? You don't?

397
00:26:51,840 --> 00:26:54,040
Okay, let's go.

398
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:57,160
Hey, happy divorce.

399
00:26:57,840 --> 00:27:00,520
And congratulations.

400
00:27:01,120 --> 00:27:05,960
Don't invite me to your wedding.
Disgusting!

401
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:15,440
No!

402
00:27:24,480 --> 00:27:27,120
Darling, are you going to eat all these?

403
00:27:30,360 --> 00:27:35,400
I need to let go of all my feelings
by eating this chicken.

404
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:40,159
No one can lay a hand on you anymore.

405
00:27:40,160 --> 00:27:42,080
You have me.

406
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:46,080
What about Farez?

407
00:27:49,400 --> 00:27:53,280
Just don't think too much about it.

408
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:56,640
He's going to get what's coming to him.

409
00:27:58,840 --> 00:28:02,000
- Do you need my help?
- Thanks, but no.

410
00:28:02,560 --> 00:28:06,399
I don't want you to be involved
with anything related to him.

411
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:08,559
Let me handle it alone. Okay?

412
00:28:08,560 --> 00:28:09,920
All right.

413
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:29,520
Fateh is awake.

414
00:28:31,400 --> 00:28:32,560
That's good.

415
00:28:33,160 --> 00:28:36,280
The police contacted me
to help with the investigation.

416
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:38,960
Isn't it nice

417
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:43,280
when all your plans work out?

418
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:46,319
Tomorrow's the press conference.

419
00:28:46,320 --> 00:28:50,399
I will announce that Thariq Ridzuwan

420
00:28:50,400 --> 00:28:53,239
is the leader
of the Gajah Hitam syndicate.

421
00:28:53,240 --> 00:28:56,160
The mastermind who's been selling
the kids from Teduh.

422
00:29:03,360 --> 00:29:05,920
Brilliant, Datin.

423
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:13,600
Tomorrow, Husniya Radwa
will hate Thariq so much.

424
00:29:14,960 --> 00:29:16,120
Farez,

425
00:29:17,320 --> 00:29:19,480
when are you going to let go of my family?

426
00:29:22,160 --> 00:29:24,000
Maybe...

427
00:29:26,120 --> 00:29:27,359
tomorrow.

428
00:29:27,360 --> 00:29:28,760
After the press conference.

429
00:29:31,800 --> 00:29:34,000
I'll be saying prayers tonight.

430
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:36,880
I feel so at peace.

431
00:29:38,600 --> 00:29:41,280
When I marry Husniya Radwa,

432
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:43,360
I will repent.

433
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:50,640
Do you think God will accept
my repentance?

434
00:30:06,520 --> 00:30:08,960
Amen.

435
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:19,280
- Do you have work today?
- I do. Why?

436
00:30:20,440 --> 00:30:22,080
Just asking.

437
00:30:24,440 --> 00:30:27,040
Darling, I'll send you to the camp today.

438
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:30,679
No need.

439
00:30:30,680 --> 00:30:32,600
Can I just stay home?

440
00:30:33,200 --> 00:30:34,920
It's dangerous.

441
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:38,919
Farez is still free.
What if he kidnaps you?

442
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:43,519
Dear, if he wants to kidnap me,
he would have done it already.

443
00:30:43,520 --> 00:30:46,560
Especially when he came
to see me all the time.

444
00:30:47,280 --> 00:30:49,479
Okay? Don't worry.

445
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:52,040
I'll be fine. I promise.

446
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:57,440
Do you love me?

447
00:31:01,560 --> 00:31:03,680
Do you trust me?

448
00:31:04,840 --> 00:31:05,800
I do.

449
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:11,040
Then, let me decide
what I'm doing today. Is that okay?

450
00:31:11,920 --> 00:31:14,040
The thing is, I'm...

451
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:16,759
I'm worried.

452
00:31:16,760 --> 00:31:18,880
Because I can't protect you.

453
00:31:20,120 --> 00:31:24,560
Do you know that you're always
protecting me with your prayers?

454
00:31:26,960 --> 00:31:29,560
No prayer

455
00:31:30,080 --> 00:31:32,480
returns empty-handed.

456
00:31:36,040 --> 00:31:37,760
You always know what to say.

457
00:31:41,640 --> 00:31:43,320
Tell me something good.

458
00:31:49,040 --> 00:31:52,080
Every hurt and wound
we accept with sincerity

459
00:31:53,600 --> 00:31:56,759
will one day be exchanged for joy.

460
00:31:56,760 --> 00:31:59,199
Leave everything to God.

461
00:31:59,200 --> 00:32:02,080
Let the plans and affairs
of heaven do their work.

462
00:32:07,120 --> 00:32:09,120
Look at all these pictures of these women.

463
00:32:09,920 --> 00:32:12,720
They're all the same height
and the same weight as Husniya.

464
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:17,000
Why are you smiling?

465
00:32:17,840 --> 00:32:19,440
Because I'm happy.

466
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:23,120
What do you mean?

467
00:32:23,800 --> 00:32:28,040
Because maybe we don't need them anymore.

468
00:32:29,160 --> 00:32:31,040
What are you trying to say?

469
00:32:41,720 --> 00:32:43,800
Peace be upon you.

470
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:46,360
And peace be upon you.

471
00:32:47,600 --> 00:32:49,359
I was looking for you at the cafe.

472
00:32:49,360 --> 00:32:51,240
You weren't there.

473
00:32:52,520 --> 00:32:54,599
Why were you looking for me?

474
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:58,279
I just need a friend to talk to.

475
00:32:58,280 --> 00:32:59,640
I need to vent.

476
00:33:00,760 --> 00:33:02,920
Where's Thariq?

477
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:08,119
I don't know.

478
00:33:08,120 --> 00:33:10,039
After I asked for a divorce,

479
00:33:10,040 --> 00:33:12,079
he got really angry.

480
00:33:12,080 --> 00:33:15,760
<i>He wouldn't talk to me. It's unfair.</i>

481
00:33:16,440 --> 00:33:19,960
He was the one at fault,
but I was the one he was mad at.

482
00:33:21,360 --> 00:33:23,760
Didn't he say anything to you?

483
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:27,960
He didn't. Why?

484
00:33:28,560 --> 00:33:30,280
Where are you right now?

485
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:36,160
At home.

486
00:33:38,120 --> 00:33:40,080
Why didn't you come
to the hospital anymore?

487
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:45,040
<i>Did you know that I was discharged</i>

488
00:33:45,960 --> 00:33:48,239
from the hospital without him?

489
00:33:48,240 --> 00:33:50,839
He's been so mean to me.

490
00:33:50,840 --> 00:33:53,079
That's enough.

491
00:33:53,080 --> 00:33:54,480
Don't be upset.

492
00:33:55,160 --> 00:33:56,999
Can I see you?

493
00:33:57,000 --> 00:33:59,440
- I want to vent again.
<i>- Sure.</i>

494
00:34:00,200 --> 00:34:01,800
Let's have dinner tonight.

495
00:34:03,120 --> 00:34:06,200
Sure, just let me know.

496
00:34:06,800 --> 00:34:08,000
Okay.

497
00:34:09,040 --> 00:34:10,198
Bye.

498
00:34:10,199 --> 00:34:11,679
<i>Radwa.</i>

499
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:14,560
Yes?

500
00:34:15,719 --> 00:34:18,560
I miss talking to you.

501
00:34:23,719 --> 00:34:24,800
Me too.

502
00:34:27,880 --> 00:34:29,560
I can't wait to see you.

503
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:32,800
Bye.

504
00:34:35,639 --> 00:34:37,560
Freaking psycho!

505
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:31,080
Boss, Thariq is here.

506
00:35:35,480 --> 00:35:37,640
Go to hell, friend.

507
00:35:55,160 --> 00:35:56,400
Hi.

508
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:58,400
Hi.

509
00:36:01,240 --> 00:36:02,520
How are you?

510
00:36:09,360 --> 00:36:12,440
How did you know
Razi got Raudhah pregnant?

511
00:36:14,920 --> 00:36:17,360
You said you're not talking
to Thariq anymore.

512
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:19,360
I lied.

513
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:23,360
So, you know everything about me?

514
00:36:26,600 --> 00:36:28,480
I love you, Husniya.

515
00:36:29,120 --> 00:36:33,480
I know your mother and your sisters
hurt you all the time.

516
00:36:34,960 --> 00:36:39,559
So I stalked them until I found out
that your sister

517
00:36:39,560 --> 00:36:42,760
was having an affair
with her own brother-in-law.

518
00:36:46,120 --> 00:36:47,280
What a psychopath.

519
00:36:49,480 --> 00:36:50,640
I was stupid.

520
00:36:52,160 --> 00:36:56,159
For sharing about my marriage
to someone I barely knew.

521
00:36:56,160 --> 00:37:00,120
I was weak and vulnerable.

522
00:37:00,800 --> 00:37:02,160
I needed a friend.

523
00:37:03,320 --> 00:37:06,600
- And I was your friend.
- You took advantage of me!

524
00:37:07,760 --> 00:37:11,160
You used my problem
with Thariq to ruin him!

525
00:37:12,720 --> 00:37:17,760
And it doesn't change the fact
that you and Thariq weren't happy.

526
00:37:19,480 --> 00:37:22,319
Don't you understand? Listen to me.

527
00:37:22,320 --> 00:37:27,440
Even if I divorce Thariq,
I will never ever go to you.

528
00:37:28,720 --> 00:37:31,560
I may not be Thariq
Ridzuwan's wife anymore,

529
00:37:32,480 --> 00:37:39,240
but my love for him will never change,
and will never stop.

530
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:52,960
If I had known that you would hurt Thariq,

531
00:37:54,160 --> 00:37:58,080
I should have let you die back then.

532
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:09,240
I, Datin Zizi Abu Samah,

533
00:38:10,320 --> 00:38:12,240
as the founder

534
00:38:13,120 --> 00:38:15,840
of the shelter for kids, Teduh,

535
00:38:16,640 --> 00:38:19,040
would like to confess that

536
00:38:21,720 --> 00:38:27,000
I have been working
with the Gajah Hitam syndicate,

537
00:38:28,840 --> 00:38:32,840
which has been trafficking
the children under my care

538
00:38:33,360 --> 00:38:34,800
to be sold overseas.

539
00:38:38,360 --> 00:38:40,600
And the person responsible

540
00:38:41,640 --> 00:38:44,920
for leading the syndicate,

541
00:38:46,840 --> 00:38:51,000
the largest child trafficking
syndicate in Asia,

542
00:38:53,960 --> 00:38:55,040
is...

543
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:01,680
You're a psychopath!

544
00:39:08,120 --> 00:39:10,120
I respect your love for Thariq.

545
00:39:15,320 --> 00:39:17,720
But loving people blindly

546
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:20,040
is dangerous.

547
00:39:22,120 --> 00:39:23,880
It can make you

548
00:39:25,600 --> 00:39:29,960
blind to their mistakes and ugliness.

549
00:39:30,720 --> 00:39:33,319
Thariq is a perfect man.

550
00:39:33,320 --> 00:39:35,319
The kindest man.

551
00:39:35,320 --> 00:39:39,120
Someone you will never be,
even until the day you die!

552
00:39:47,840 --> 00:39:49,280
Tonight,

553
00:39:51,480 --> 00:39:55,520
you will find out who Thariq really is.

554
00:40:10,720 --> 00:40:12,320
Muhammad Farez.

555
00:40:26,760 --> 00:40:30,920
Because you know my Mom,

556
00:40:31,760 --> 00:40:34,359
and I have so much respect for you,

557
00:40:34,360 --> 00:40:36,160
I will let you go.

558
00:40:52,360 --> 00:40:53,600
Yes.

559
00:40:55,560 --> 00:40:59,080
I lied. I will never let you go.

560
00:41:01,360 --> 00:41:02,520
You are...

561
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:06,680
the cruelest person
I've ever met in my life.

562
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:09,920
Now,

563
00:41:11,080 --> 00:41:12,520
tell me.

564
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:16,400
Are you going to help me

565
00:41:17,400 --> 00:41:19,440
arrest the leader of Gajah Hitam?

566
00:41:21,040 --> 00:41:22,800
Farez.

567
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:31,560
What did he take from you?

568
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:37,360
You're not talking
because he threatened you, right?

569
00:41:43,920 --> 00:41:45,400
What did he do to you?

570
00:42:04,320 --> 00:42:05,240
Hurry up!

571
00:42:15,360 --> 00:42:18,920
- Is it done?
- Boss, Holy Dragon saved Zizi's family.

572
00:42:24,280 --> 00:42:25,159
Radwa!

573
00:42:25,160 --> 00:42:29,359
You'd rather watch me die
than live with Thariq, right?

574
00:42:29,360 --> 00:42:31,279
So kill me!

575
00:42:31,280 --> 00:42:33,320
Kill me now!

576
00:42:34,120 --> 00:42:36,040
Boss, we have to leave.

577
00:42:37,040 --> 00:42:38,359
We got caught.

578
00:42:38,360 --> 00:42:41,079
Datin Zizi exposed us
at the press conference.

579
00:42:41,080 --> 00:42:43,679
She said you're the leader of Gajah Hitam.

580
00:42:43,680 --> 00:42:45,320
Now, everyone knows.

581
00:43:25,520 --> 00:43:27,360
Are you angry that I went out?

582
00:43:31,120 --> 00:43:32,880
Do you want to know where I went?

583
00:43:38,040 --> 00:43:39,800
Then why are you waiting out here?

584
00:43:41,280 --> 00:43:42,680
Because I wanted to make sure
that you're safe.

585
00:43:45,760 --> 00:43:47,200
Why aren't you angry?

586
00:43:48,480 --> 00:43:51,239
I told you, darling.

587
00:43:51,240 --> 00:43:53,160
Just do whatever you want.

588
00:43:54,080 --> 00:43:56,320
Plus, I believe in you

589
00:43:57,320 --> 00:43:59,359
and I love you so much.

590
00:43:59,360 --> 00:44:01,120
You are a woman.

591
00:44:01,760 --> 00:44:03,040
Women are special.

592
00:44:04,160 --> 00:44:08,280
A woman has no limit
to her love for someone.

593
00:44:09,320 --> 00:44:11,159
I'm not upset.

594
00:44:11,160 --> 00:44:13,560
I'm thankful. Thankful for you.

595
00:44:16,560 --> 00:44:17,840
Dear.

596
00:44:18,560 --> 00:44:19,800
Yes.

597
00:44:21,360 --> 00:44:23,000
I'm pregnant.

598
00:44:27,800 --> 00:44:31,880
{\an8}TO BE CONTINUED

599
00:44:38,360 --> 00:44:40,760
{\an8}Have I ever not given you
anything you want? No, right?

600
00:44:41,400 --> 00:44:44,239
{\an8}Just tell me what you want. Tell me.

601
00:44:44,240 --> 00:44:45,560
{\an8}I want to ride in a tank.

602
00:44:46,440 --> 00:44:48,039
{\an8}<i>Two of our men were sent to Sabah.</i>

603
00:44:48,040 --> 00:44:50,679
{\an8}<i>They should have been back three days ago,</i>

604
00:44:50,680 --> 00:44:52,319
{\an8}but we haven't heard from them.

605
00:44:52,320 --> 00:44:53,799
{\an8}<i>I'm on leave now.</i>

606
00:44:53,800 --> 00:44:56,039
{\an8}<i>Radwa could give birth at any time now.</i>

607
00:44:56,040 --> 00:44:58,279
{\an8}This is a non-negotiable order, Ridz.

608
00:44:58,280 --> 00:45:01,719
{\an8}Bring our men back.

609
00:45:01,720 --> 00:45:02,879
{\an8}I don't want to go.

610
00:45:02,880 --> 00:45:05,400
{\an8}You have to go, dear.

611
00:45:06,720 --> 00:45:08,680
{\an8}I love you so much.

612
00:45:10,880 --> 00:45:12,800
{\an8}I love you more.

